						               													<description>Yavalanchor is a Yavalath derivative for 2 players that can be played with the same set of components (hexhex board of size 5 and counters in 3 colours).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULES&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SETUP&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has an allocated colour (White and Black). Red counters are neutral and will act as 'anchors'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting with White players take turns placing either:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) A red counter in ANY empty cell or...&amp;#10;b) A counter of their colour in an empty cell adjacent to a red counter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;...until the victory condition is reached.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME END&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a 5-in-a-row containing only counters of a player colour AND red is created. The owner of that colour is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the rare case of several lines being created, the player that placed the last counter chooses the winning line.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the board fills up before reaching this victory condition the game ends in a draw.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
